    "sub_topic": "Finding the Hamiltonian cycle in a graph.",
    "message_1": "Consider a complete graph with 5 vertices, where the weight of each edge is given in the following matrix:\n\n```\n   0  2  7  3  6\n   2  0  4  8  5\n   7  4  0  1  9\n   3  8  1  0  2\n   6  5  9  2  0\n```\n\nFind the Hamiltonian cycle of minimum weight in this graph.",
    "message_2": "To find the Hamiltonian cycle of minimum weight, we need to find a cycle that visits each vertex exactly once and returns to the starting vertex, with the minimum total weight.\n\nWe can use the brute force method to find all possible Hamiltonian cycles and then choose the one with the minimum weight. There are (5-1)! = 4! = 24 possible Hamiltonian cycles in a complete graph with 5 vertices.\n\nHere are all the possible Hamiltonian cycles and their weights:\n\n1. 0-1-2-3-4-0: 2+4+1+2+6 = 15\n2. 0-1-2-4-3-0: 2+4+9+2+3 = 20\n3. 0-1-3-2-4-0: 2+8+1+9+6 = 26\n4. 0-1-3-4-2-0: 2+8+2+9+7 = 28\n5. 0-1-4-2-3-0: 2+5+9+1+3 = 20\n6. 0-1-4-3-2-0: 2+5+2+1+7 = 17\n\n7. 0-2-1-3-4-0: 7+4+8+2+6 = 27\n8. 0-2-1-4-3-0: 7+4+5+2+3 = 21\n9. 0-2-3-1-4-0: 7+1+8+5+6 = 27\n10. 0-2-3-4-1-0: 7+1+2+9+4 = 23\n11. 0-2-4-1-3-0: 7+9+5+8+3 = 32\n12. 0-2-4-3-1-0: 7+9+2+1+4 = 23\n\n13. 0-3-1-2-4-0: 3+8+4+9+6 = 30\n14. 0-3-1-4-2-0: 3+8+5+9+7 = 32\n15. 0-3-2-1-4-0: 3+1+4+5+6 = 19\n16. 0-3-2-4-1-0: 3+1+9+9+4 = 26\n17. 0-3-4-1-2-0: 3+2+5+4+7 = 21\n18. 0-3-4-2-1-0: 3+2+9+9+4 = 27\n\n19. 0-4-1-2-3-0: 6+5+4+1+3 = 19\n20. 0-4-1-3-2-0: 6+5+8+1+7 = 27\n21. 0-4-2-1-3-0: 6+9+4+8+3 = 30\n22. 0-4-2-3-1-0: 6+9+1+1+4 = 21\n23. 0-4-3-1-2-0: 6+2+8+4+7 = 27\n24. 0-4-3-2-1-0: 6+2+1+1+4 = 14\n\nThe Hamiltonian cycle with the minimum weight is 0-4-3-2-1-0 with a weight of 14."
